20their%20taps%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Ffluoridation%2Fphp%2Fstatistics%2F2022-water-fluoridation-statistics.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECenters%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%3C%2Fa%3E%20(CDC).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20health%20experts%20describe%20fluoridated%20water%20%E2%80%94%20a%20voluntary%20practice%20for%20local%20water%20districts%20%E2%80%94%20as%20one%20of%20modern%20medicine's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fmmwr%2Fpreview%2Fmmwrhtml%2Fmm4850bx.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreatest%20public%20health%20achievements%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20up%20there%20with%20the%20recognition%20that%20smoking%20is%20bad%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobert-f-kennedy-jr-views-vaccines-autism-testing-debunked-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKennedy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20environmental%20lawyer%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20the%20fight%20to%20clean%20up%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.riverkeeper.org%2Fblogs%2Fhonoring-our-foundation-in-science%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHudson%20River%20in%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20there's%20no%20need%20to%20fluoridate%20drinking%20water%20anymore%20since%20most%20toothpaste%20contains%20fluoride.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20not%20alone.%20An%20important%20debate%20over%20fluoride%20is%20gaining%20fresh%20steam%20among%20scientists%20and%20legal%20experts.%20Some%20recent%20studies%20suggest%20more%20research%20is%20still%20needed%20on%20safe%20fluoride%20levels%20for%20kids.%20Plus%2C%20a%20federal%20ruling%20in%20California%20this%20year%20questioned%20the%20US%20government's%20recommended%20dose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20medical%20professionals%20%E2%80%94%20chiefly%20dentists%20%E2%80%94%20support%20some%20level%20of%20fluoridation%2C%20there%20is%20growing%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eagreement%20that%20we%20still%20aren't%20sure%20how%20much%20fluoride%20is%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2273e9cfea-f185-4392-8a29-deb966cdc1f8%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Why%20did%20we%20start%20fluoridating%20water%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E120%20years%20ago%2C%20fluoride%20was%20the%20mystery%20culprit%20behind%20brown%20teeth%20in%20Colorado%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221912%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22woman%20with%20brown%20teeth%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672ea140192f525898574da1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222752%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20little%20bit%20of%20fluoride%20strengthens%20teeth%2C%20but%20too%20much%20fluoride%20can%20cause%20fluorosis%20poisoning%20and%20tooth%20decay.%20That's%20what%20happened%20to%20this%20woman%20living%20in%20Zhijin%20county%2C%20China.%3Cp%3EMark%20Ralston%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20most%20Americans%20have%20fluoride%20in%20their%20drinking%20water%20stretches%20back%20more%20than%20a%20century%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nidcr.nih.gov%2Fhealth-info%2Ffluoride%2Fthe-story-of-fluoridation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emysterious%20outbreak%3C%2Fa%3E%20scattered%20across%20the%20Midwest%20and%20western%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%201900s%2C%20dentists%20started%20noticing%20that%20children%20in%20specific%20towns%2C%20including%20Colorado%20Springs%2C%20Colorado%3B%20Oakley%2C%20Idaho%3B%20and%20Bauxite%2C%20Arkansas%2C%20were%20developing%20hard%2C%20chocolate-colored%20teeth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20more%20than%2020%20years%2C%20but%20eventually%2C%20researchers%20discovered%20that%20these%20unusual%20brown%20stains%20were%20caused%20by%20high%20amounts%20of%20naturally%20occurring%20fluoride%20in%20the%20drinking%20water%20in%20certain%20areas%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20found%20that%20the%20fluoride%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mineral%20compound%20found%20in%20rocks%20and%20dirt%20%E2%80%94%20was%20strengthening%20teeth.%20It%20was%20hardening%20tooth%20enamel%20and%20helping%20to%20repair%20some%20early-stage%20tooth%20decay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201945%2C%20scientists%20had%20learned%20enough%20about%20fluoride%20to%20harness%20the%20technique%20to%20prevent%20cavities%20for%20the%20masses.%20They%20proposed%20microdosing%20the%20mineral%20into%20the%20public%20water%20supply%20to%20give%20kids%20just%20enough%20fluoride%20to%20protect%20their%20teeth%20and%20help%20heal%20dental%20decay%20without%20giving%20them%20so%20much%20that%20their%20teeth%20would%20go%20brown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experiment%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201945%2C%20Grand%20Rapids%2C%20Michigan%2C%20was%20the%20first%20city%20to%20purposefully%20fluoridate%20its%20water.%20In%20the%20first%2010%20years%20of%20the%20program%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20cavities%20in%20kids%20decreased%20by%20more%20than%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC1551218%2F%3Fpage%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E60%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Thus%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20fluoridated%20water%20as%20a%20boon%20for%20public%20health%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ffc42276-b971-4331-bd76-9f4c2877d29f%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Who%20decides%20fluoride%20levels%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%20water%20districts%20decide%20their%20own%20fluoride%20levels%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22tap%20water%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672ea19788cea3ba1c1f8792%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMost%20Americans%20have%20fluoridated%20tap%20water.%20Dentists%20say%20it's%20a%20great%20way%20to%20avoid%20dental%20decay.%3Cp%3ELeonard%20Ortiz%2FMediaNews%20Group%2FOrange%20County%20Register%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FRobertKennedyJr%2Fstatus%2F1852812012478398923%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20he'd%20aim%20to%20convince%20local%20authorities%20nationwide%20to%20remove%20any%20added%20fluoride%20from%20taps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20fluoride%20is%20on%20its%20way%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Kennedy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fvideo%2Frfk-jr-talks-health-care-agenda-following-trump-win-223717957893%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20NBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20News%20the%20day%20after%20the%20election%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20going%20to%20compel%20anybody%20to%20take%20it%20out%2C%20but%20I'm%20going%20to%20advise%20the%20water%20districts.%20I'm%20going%20to%20give%20them%20good%20information%20about%20the%20science%2C%20and%20I%20think%20fluoride%20will%20disappear.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20does%20not%20control%20water%20supplies%20in%20the%20US.%20That%20task%20is%20up%20to%20states%20and%20local%20water%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20does%20mandate%20a%20limit%20for%20fluoride%20in%20tap%20water%3A%20four%20milligrams%20per%20liter.%20That%20limit%20is%20meant%20to%20prevent%20crippling%20health%20issues%20caused%20by%20excess%20fluoride%20intake%2C%20like%20a%20bone-weakening%20disease%20called%20skeletal%20fluorosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e730cbbb-f6d0-4962-9881-0475436e9095%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Why%20did%20the%20US%20lower%20fluoride%20levels%3F%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20lowered%20fluoride%20levels%20in%20drinking%20water%20in%202015%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223531%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22crest%20toothpaste%20vintage%20ad%20w%20nina%20simone%20and%20daughter%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673266f3192f52589857abfe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224416%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECrest%20was%20the%20first%20toothpaste%20developed%20with%20fluoride.%20Jazz%20singer%20Nina%20Simone%20starred%20in%20a%20Crest%20ad%20in%201964%2C%20roughly%20eight%20years%20after%20the%20toothpaste%20hit%20the%20market%20nationwide.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Ochs%20Archives%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amount%20of%20fluoride%20added%20to%20a%20water%20supply%20varies%20not%20only%20by%20city%20and%20county%20but%20also%20by%20the%20individual%20water%20system%20supplying%20a%20given%20neighborhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20years%2C%20the%20federal%20recommendation%20fluctuated%20based%20on%20location.%20In%20warmer%20climates%20%E2%80%94%20where%20it%20was%20assumed%20that%20kids%20consumed%20more%20water%20to%20stay%20cool%20%E2%80%94%20officials%20recommended%200.7%20milligrams%20of%20fluoride%20per%20liter.%20Colder%20areas%20were%20advised%20to%20add%201.2%20milligrams%20per%20liter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20reviewing%20evidence%20in%202015%2C%20the%20US%20Public%20Health%20Service%20decided%20that%20the%20discrepancy%20wasn't%20needed.%20The%20recommendation%20for%20fluoridation%20is%20now%20set%20at%200.7%20milligrams%20per%20liter%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20major%20cities%20in%20the%20US%20hover%20around%20the%200.7%20figure.%20Some%20places%20naturally%20have%20elevated%20levels%20of%20fluoride%20in%20their%20water%20due%20to%20geological%20factors.%20In%20Lordsburg%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20for%20example%2C%20water%20samples%20collected%20earlier%20this%20year%20had%20concentrations%20of%20fluoride%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcityoflordsburg.com%2Ffluoride-mcl-notice-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E5.2%20and%206.4%20milligrams%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20liter.%20Authorities%20there%20advise%20that%20children%20under%209%20years%20old%20shouldn't%20drink%20tap%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c03fabfb-6a1d-488a-8229-718ca0e2727d%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What's%20up%20in%20places%20with%20fluoride-free%20water%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlaces%20with%20fluoride-free%20water%20generally%20have%20worse%20dental%20health%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224813%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22toothbrush%20with%20paste%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672ea1ea5ec9bfa3d63cf2b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223209%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMost%20toothpaste%20has%20fluoride%20in%20it.%3Cp%3EMatthias%20Balk%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EProponents%20of%20ditching%20fluoride%20often%20point%20to%20the%20many%20European%20countries%20that%20do%20not%20fluoridate%20their%20water.%20Those%20countries%20are%20not%20100%25%20fluoride-free%2C%20though%3A%20unlike%20people%20in%20the%20US%2C%20many%20Europeans%20consume%20fluoridated%20salt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHawaii%20is%20the%20only%20US%20state%20without%20any%20fluoride%20in%20municipal%20taps%3B%20fluoridated%20water%20is%20only%20available%20there%20on%20military%20bases.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealth.hawaii.gov%2Fabout%2Ffiles%2F2013%2F06%2FHawaii-Smiles-Report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2015%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Hawaii's%20health%20department%20said%20the%20state%20also%20has%20the%20highest%20prevalence%20of%20tooth%20decay%20among%203rd%20graders%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20obvious%3B%20you%20can%20see%20it%20in%20the%20quality%20of%20their%20enamel%2C%26quot%3B%20Anthony%20Kim%2C%20dental%20director%20at%20the%20Waimanalo%20Health%20Clinic%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.civilbeat.org%2F2020%2F02%2Fwhy-hawaii-continues-to-keep-fluoride-out-of-its-drinking-water%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHonolulu%20Civil%20Beat%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BSadly%2C%20especially%20among%20the%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20in%20Canada%20see%20the%20same%20phenomenon.%20The%20rate%20of%20cavities%20detected%20in%20Alberta%20spiked%20after%20the%20city%20went%20fluoride-free%20in%202011%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.17269%2Fs41997-024-00858-w%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFebruary%202024%20study%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Calgary%20did%20the%20same%20and%20saw%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC9542152%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilar%20tooth%20issues%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20kids.%20The%20city%20now%20plans%20to%20re-fluoridate%20its%20water%20supply%2C%20but%20cost%20issues%20and%20global%20supply%20chain%20problems%20post-pandemic%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcalgary.ctvnews.ca%2Fcalgary-s-plan-to-reintroduce-fluoride-into-drinking-water-pushed-back-to-2025-1.6845098%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreated%20delays%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20military%20supports%20fluoridation.%20In%202016%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Filikemyteeth.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2013%2F05%2FDoD-Fluoridation-Memo-March-2013.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Defense%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0said%C2%A0dental%20decay%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%26quot%3B%20reason%20military%20personnel%20were%20classified%20as%20non-deployable.%20As%20such%2C%20fluoridated%20water%20is%20now%20mandated%20on%20any%20military%20base%20with%20more%20than%203%2C300%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERumors%20have%20circulated%20that%20drinking%20fluoridated%20water%20can%20lead%20to%20bone%20cancer%20(osteosarcoma)%2C%20but%20long-term%20studies%20from%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fije%2Farticle%2F43%2F1%2F224%2F736028%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20UK%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1877782111001822%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%3C%2Fa%3E%20haven't%20found%20any%20credible%20evidence%20of%20higher%20rates%20in%20areas%20where%20people%20drink%20fluoridated%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22726f1d49-c5ff-447d-b2cc-6cf2412f9906%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Is%20there%20truth%20to%20claims%20of%20IQ%20issues%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20there%20any%20truth%20to%20claims%20of%20IQ%20issues%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223594%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22anti%20fluoride%20protesters%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672ea4af192f525898574dcc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%201966%2C%20a%20small%20group%20of%20Australian%20protesters%20flocked%20to%20their%20local%20health%20department%20to%20protest%20fluoridation.%20Australia%20still%20puts%20fluoride%20in%20the%20water%20today%2C%20as%20do%20most%20US%20water%20systems.%3Cp%3EFrank%20Albert%20Charles%20Burke%2FFairfax%20Media%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20November%202%2C%20Kennedy%20said%20on%20X%20that%20fluoride%20is%20an%20%26quot%3Bindustrial%20waste%26quot%3B%20that%20is%20linked%20to%20%26quot%3BIQ%20loss.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20linked%20to%20a%20ruling%20from%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20California%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cand.uscourts.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2F17-cv-2162-Food-_-Water-Watch-Inc.-et-al.-v.-EPA-et-al-Opinion.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOctober.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20judge%2C%20appointed%20by%20former%20President%20Obama%2C%20said%20that%20while%20he%20could%20not%20%26quot%3Bconclude%20with%20certainty%26quot%3B%20that%20fluoridated%20water%20could%20reduce%20the%20IQ%20of%20children%2C%20there%20is%20evidence%20that%20it%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bhazardous%20at%20dosages%20that%20are%20far%20too%20close%20to%20fluoride%20levels%20in%20the%20drinking%20water%20of%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20ruling%20came%20weeks%20after%20a%20headline-grabbing%20paper%20in%20which%20a%20group%20of%20independent%20scientists%20reviewed%20existing%20evidence%20on%20fluoridation%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fntp.niehs.nih.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-08%2Ffluoride_final_508.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20National%20Toxicology%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Their%20review%20concluded%20that%20some%20studies%20of%20fluoride%20consumption%20have%20found%20links%20between%20higher%20fluoride%20water%20levels%20and%20lower%20IQs%20in%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20couple%20of%20big%20caveats%20to%20keep%20in%20mind.%20First%2C%20those%20studies%20were%20conducted%20in%20other%20countries%2C%20including%20Canada%2C%20China%2C%20India%2C%20Iran%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20Mexico%2C%20not%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20association%20with%20lower%20IQs%20was%20only%20apparent%20when%20children%20were%20drinking%20water%20loaded%20with%20fluoride%2C%20at%20more%20than%201.5%20milligrams%20per%20liter.%20That's%20double%20what's%20recommended%20in%20the%20US%20and%2050%25%20more%20fluoride%20than%20what%20was%20first%20used%20in%20Grand%20Rapids%20in%201945.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20studies%20are%20needed%20to%20fully%20understand%20the%20potential%20for%20lower%20fluoride%20exposure%20to%20affect%20children's%20IQ%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20new%20studies%20are%20starting%20to%20trickle%20out.%20Fluoride%20and%20aluminum%20researcher%20Ashley%20Malin%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20epidemiology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Florida%2C%20recently%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F38767917%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20potential%20link%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20a%20woman's%20fluoride%20levels%20during%20pregnancy%20and%20neurobehavioral%20problems%20in%20her%20toddler%20three%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20this%20point%2C%20I%20would%20advise%20that%20pregnant%20women%20reduce%20their%20fluoride%20intake%2C%26quot%3B%20Malin%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMalin%20brushes%20her%20teeth%20without%20fluoride%2C%20drinks%20filtered%20water%20(using%20a%20reverse%20osmosis%20water%20purifier%20or%20buying%20bottled%20water)%2C%20and%20says%20that%20the%20most%20fluoride%20she%20consumes%20is%20probably%20from%20the%20black%20chai%20tea%20she%20occasionally%20drinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b5f129c-cdf6-4dba-a89c-6887474b296d%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20is%20the%20right%20dose%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESettling%20on%20the%20right%20dose%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222487%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22retro%20photo%20of%20kid%20brushing%20teeth%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672ea298192f525898574db4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20third-grade%20student%20brushes%20his%20teeth%20in%20a%20program%20using%20specially%20formulated%20fluoride%20toothpaste%20to%20reduce%20dental%20decay%20among%20schoolchildren%2C%20circa%201969.%3Cp%3EOliva%20Fall%2FThe%20Denver%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20tease%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cochrane.org%2FCD010856%2FORAL_does-adding-fluoride-water-supplies-prevent-tooth-decay%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexactly%20how%20beneficial%20fluoridated%20water%20is%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20preventing%20cavities%2C%20in%20part%20because%20fluoridating%20water%20isn't%20the%20only%20way%20that%20tooth%20care%20has%20improved%20dramatically%20since%20the%201940s.%20(The%20level%20of%20fluoride%20in%20many%20toothpastes%20is%20much%20higher%20than%20what's%20in%20the%20water.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20California%20ruling%20last%20month%20didn't%20get%20prescriptive%20about%20what%20the%20EPA%20should%20do%20about%20all%20this%20uncertainty.%20It%20only%20recommended%20some%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Bregulatory%20action%26quot%3B%20on%20fluoride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20should%20be%20noted%20that%20this%20finding%20does%20not%20conclude%20with%20certainty%20that%20fluoridated%20water%20is%20injurious%20to%20public%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20verdict%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20wants%20the%20EPA%20to%20better%20answer%20now%20whether%200.7%20milligrams%20per%20liter%20of%20fluoride%20is%20safe%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20EPA%20has%20said%20in%20the%20past%20that%20reviewing%20their%20fluoride%20numbers%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Blow%20priority%26quot%3B%20item%20for%20the%20agency.%20Public%20health%20experts%20and%20dentists%20generally%20agree%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nidcr.nih.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnidcr-news%2F2024%2Fbig-hopes-little-teeth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efluoridated%20tap%20water%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20safe%2C%20effortless%2C%20and%20equitable%20way%20to%20ensure%20people%20get%20enough%20fluoride%20to%20prevent%20most%20childhood%20cavities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20scientists%20haven't%20quite%20settled%20on%20the%20optimal%20fluoride%20level%20in%20tap%20water%20to%20maintain%20healthy%20teeth%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffluoride-in-water-why-it-is-controversial-risks-benefits-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731446585000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672ea6645ec9bfa3d63cf31d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffluoride-in-water-why-it-is-controversial-risks-benefits-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Too%20much%20fluoride%20can%20make%20your%20teeth%20brown%2C%20but%20getting%20a%20little%20bit%20is%20a%20dentist's%20dream.%20Here's%20the%20complete%20history%20of%20fluoridated%20water.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbrueck%40businessinsider.com%20(Hilary%20Brueck)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%