%2C%20along%20with%20Sikander%E2%80%99s%20antics%2C%20features%20recipes%20of%20historic%20South%20Asian%20dishes%20and%20culinary%20traditions%20shared%20by%20virtuosos%20across%20the%20subcontinent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Echats%20with%20cultural%20historian%20Dr%20Tarana%20Husain%20Khan%2C%20who%20has%20co-edited%20this%20literary%20work%20of%20art%20along%20with%20Siobhan%20Lambert-Hurley%2C%20professor%20of%20global%20history%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Sheffield%20and%20Claire%20Chambers%2C%20professor%20of%20global%20literature%20at%20the%20University%20of%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EResuscitating%20forgotten%20foods%20through%20narratives%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECelebrating%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F229381%2Fzero-waste-how-to-cook-cooking-tips-traditional-indian-food-using-leftovers-mother-grandmother-recipes-ang136%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20artistry%20of%20home%20cooking%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EForgotten%20Foods%3C%2Fem%3E%20marks%20just%20one%20triumph%20in%20Tarana%E2%80%99s%20diverse%20culinary%20journey.%20Previously%2C%20she%20authored%20the%20critically%20acclaimed%20%3Cem%3EDegh%20to%20Dastarkhwan%3A%20Qissas%20and%20Recipes%20from%20Rampur%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%20and%20won%20the%20Kalinga%20Literary%20Award%20for%20her%20historical%20fiction%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Begum%20and%20the%20Dastan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2021).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20firm%20believer%20that%20serendipity%20often%20makes%20for%20the%20best%20stories%20%E2%80%94%20and%20recipes%2C%20Tarana%20shares%20the%20role%20fate%20played%20in%20her%20journey%2C%20recalling%20a%20chance%20visit%20to%20the%20Rampur%20Raza%20Library%20years%20ago.%20This%2C%20she%20says%2C%20marked%20an%20inflection%20point%20of%20her